59 void ptx_thread_info::set_reg( const symbol *reg, const ptx_reg_t &value )
60 {
61  assert( reg != NULL );
62  if( reg->name() == "_" ) return;
63  assert( !m_regs.empty() );
64  assert( reg->uid() > 0 );
65  m_regs.back()[ reg ] = value;
66  if (m_enable_debug_trace )
67  m_debug_trace_regs_modified.back()[ reg ] = value;
68  m_last_set_operand_value = value;
69 }

71 ptx_reg_t ptx_thread_info::get_reg( const symbol *reg )
72 {
73  static bool unfound_register_warned = false;
74  assert( reg != NULL );
75  assert( !m_regs.empty() );
76  reg_map_t::iterator regs_iter = m_regs.back().find(reg);
77  if (regs_iter == m_regs.back().end()) {
78  assert( reg->type()->get_key().is_reg() );
79  const std::string &name = reg->name();
80  unsigned call_uid = m_callstack.back().m_call_uid;
81  ptx_reg_t uninit_reg;
82  uninit_reg.u32 = 0x0;
83  set_reg(reg, uninit_reg); // give it a value since we are going to warn the user anyway
84  std::string file_loc = get_location();
85  if( !unfound_register_warned ) {
86  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: WARNING (%s) ** reading undefined register \'%s\' (cuid:%u). Setting to 0X00000000. This is okay if you are simulating the native ISA"
87  "\n",
88  file_loc.c_str(), name.c_str(), call_uid );
89  unfound_register_warned = true;
90  }
91  regs_iter = m_regs.back().find(reg);
92  }
93  if (m_enable_debug_trace )
94  m_debug_trace_regs_read.back()[ reg ] = regs_iter->second;
95  return regs_iter->second;
96 }

98 ptx_reg_t ptx_thread_info::get_operand_value( const operand_info &op, operand_info dstInfo, unsigned opType, ptx_thread_info *thread, int derefFlag )
99 {
100  ptx_reg_t result, tmp;
101 
102 
103  if(op.get_double_operand_type() == 0) {
104  if(((opType != BB128_TYPE) && (opType != BB64_TYPE) && (opType != FF64_TYPE)) || (op.get_addr_space() != undefined_space)) {
105  if ( op.is_reg() ) {
106  result = get_reg( op.get_symbol() );
107  } else if ( op.is_builtin()) {
108  result.u32 = get_builtin( op.get_int(), op.get_addr_offset() );
109  } else if(op.is_immediate_address()){
110  result.u64 = op.get_addr_offset();
111  } else if ( op.is_memory_operand() ) {
112  // a few options here...
113  const symbol *sym = op.get_symbol();
114  const type_info *type = sym->type();
115  const type_info_key &info = type->get_key();
116 
117  if ( info.is_reg() ) {
118  const symbol *name = op.get_symbol();
119  result.u64 = get_reg(name).u64 + op.get_addr_offset();
120  } else if ( info.is_param_kernel() ) {
121  result.u64 = sym->get_address() + op.get_addr_offset();
122  } else if ( info.is_param_local() ) {
123  result.u64 = sym->get_address() + op.get_addr_offset();
124  } else if ( info.is_global() ) {
125  assert( op.get_addr_offset() == 0 );
126  result.u64 = sym->get_address();
127  } else if ( info.is_local() ) {
128  result.u64 = sym->get_address() + op.get_addr_offset();
129  } else if ( info.is_const() ) {
130  result.u64 = sym->get_address() + op.get_addr_offset();
131  } else if ( op.is_shared() ) {
132  result.u64 = op.get_symbol()->get_address() + op.get_addr_offset();
133  } else {
134  const char *name = op.name().c_str();
135  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: ERROR ** get_operand_value : unknown memory operand type for %s\n", name );
136  abort();
137  }
138 
139  } else if ( op.is_literal() ) {
140  result = op.get_literal_value();
141  } else if ( op.is_label() ) {
142  result.u64 = op.get_symbol()->get_address();
143  } else if ( op.is_shared() ) {
144  result.u64 = op.get_symbol()->get_address();
145  } else if ( op.is_const() ) {
146  result.u64 = op.get_symbol()->get_address();
147  } else if ( op.is_global() ) {
148  result.u64 = op.get_symbol()->get_address();
149  } else if ( op.is_local() ) {
150  result.u64 = op.get_symbol()->get_address();
151  } else {
152  const char *name = op.name().c_str();
153  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: ERROR ** get_operand_value : unknown operand type for %s\n", name );
154  assert(0);
155  }
156 
157  if(op.get_operand_lohi() == 1)
158  result.u64 = result.u64 & 0xFFFF;
159  else if(op.get_operand_lohi() == 2)
160  result.u64 = (result.u64>>16) & 0xFFFF;
161  } else if (opType == BB128_TYPE) {
162  // b128
163  result.u128.lowest = get_reg( op.vec_symbol(0) ).u32;
164  result.u128.low = get_reg( op.vec_symbol(1) ).u32;
165  result.u128.high = get_reg( op.vec_symbol(2) ).u32;
166  result.u128.highest = get_reg( op.vec_symbol(3) ).u32;
167  } else {
168  // bb64 or ff64
169  result.bits.ls = get_reg( op.vec_symbol(0) ).u32;
170  result.bits.ms = get_reg( op.vec_symbol(1) ).u32;
171  }
172  } else if (op.get_double_operand_type() == 1) {
173  ptx_reg_t firstHalf, secondHalf;
174  firstHalf.u64 = get_reg( op.vec_symbol(0) ).u64;
175  secondHalf.u64 = get_reg( op.vec_symbol(1) ).u64;
176  if(op.get_operand_lohi() == 1)
177  secondHalf.u64 = secondHalf.u64 & 0xFFFF;
178  else if(op.get_operand_lohi() == 2)
179  secondHalf.u64 = (secondHalf.u64>>16) & 0xFFFF;
180  result.u64 = firstHalf.u64 + secondHalf.u64;
181  } else if (op.get_double_operand_type() == 2) {
182  // s[reg1 += reg2]
183  // reg1 is incremented after value is returned: the value returned is s[reg1]
184  ptx_reg_t firstHalf, secondHalf;
185  firstHalf.u64 = get_reg(op.vec_symbol(0)).u64;
186  secondHalf.u64 = get_reg(op.vec_symbol(1)).u64;
187  if(op.get_operand_lohi() == 1)
188  secondHalf.u64 = secondHalf.u64 & 0xFFFF;
189  else if(op.get_operand_lohi() == 2)
190  secondHalf.u64 = (secondHalf.u64>>16) & 0xFFFF;
191  result.u64 = firstHalf.u64;
192  firstHalf.u64 = firstHalf.u64 + secondHalf.u64;
193  set_reg(op.vec_symbol(0),firstHalf);
194  } else if (op.get_double_operand_type() == 3) {
195  // s[reg += immediate]
196  // reg is incremented after value is returned: the value returned is s[reg]
197  ptx_reg_t firstHalf;
198  firstHalf.u64 = get_reg(op.get_symbol()).u64;
199  result.u64 = firstHalf.u64;
200  firstHalf.u64 = firstHalf.u64 + op.get_addr_offset();
201  set_reg(op.get_symbol(),firstHalf);
202  }
203 
204  ptx_reg_t finalResult;
205  memory_space *mem = NULL;
206  size_t size=0;
207  int t=0;
208  finalResult.u64=0;
209 
210  //complete other cases for reading from memory, such as reading from other const memory
211  if((op.get_addr_space() == global_space)&&(derefFlag)) {
212  // global memory - g[4], g[$r0]
213  mem = thread->get_global_memory();
214  type_info_key::type_decode(opType,size,t);
215  mem->read(result.u32,size/8,&finalResult.u128);
216  thread->m_last_effective_address = result.u32;
217  thread->m_last_memory_space = global_space;
218 
219  if( opType == S16_TYPE || opType == S32_TYPE )
220  sign_extend(finalResult,size,dstInfo);
221  } else if((op.get_addr_space() == shared_space)&&(derefFlag)) {
222  // shared memory - s[4], s[$r0]
223  mem = thread->m_shared_mem;
224  type_info_key::type_decode(opType,size,t);
225  mem->read(result.u32,size/8,&finalResult.u128);
226  thread->m_last_effective_address = result.u32;
227  thread->m_last_memory_space = shared_space;
228 
229  if( opType == S16_TYPE || opType == S32_TYPE )
230  sign_extend(finalResult,size,dstInfo);
231  } else if((op.get_addr_space() == const_space)&&(derefFlag)) {
232  // const memory - ce0c1[4], ce0c1[$r0]
233  mem = thread->get_global_memory();
234  type_info_key::type_decode(opType,size,t);
235  mem->read((result.u32 + op.get_const_mem_offset()),size/8,&finalResult.u128);
236  thread->m_last_effective_address = result.u32;
237  thread->m_last_memory_space = const_space;
238  if( opType == S16_TYPE || opType == S32_TYPE )
239  sign_extend(finalResult,size,dstInfo);
240  } else if((op.get_addr_space() == local_space)&&(derefFlag)) {
241  // local memory - l0[4], l0[$r0]
242  mem = thread->m_local_mem;
243  type_info_key::type_decode(opType,size,t);
244  mem->read(result.u32,size/8,&finalResult.u128);
245  thread->m_last_effective_address = result.u32;
246  thread->m_last_memory_space = local_space;
247  if( opType == S16_TYPE || opType == S32_TYPE )
248  sign_extend(finalResult,size,dstInfo);
249  } else {
250  finalResult = result;
251  }
252 
253  if((op.get_operand_neg() == true)&&(derefFlag)) {
254  switch( opType ) {
255  // Default to f32 for now, need to add support for others
256  case S8_TYPE:
257  case U8_TYPE:
258  case B8_TYPE:
259  finalResult.s8 = -finalResult.s8;
260  break;
261  case S16_TYPE:
262  case U16_TYPE:
263  case B16_TYPE:
264  finalResult.s16 = -finalResult.s16;
265  break;
266  case S32_TYPE:
267  case U32_TYPE:
268  case B32_TYPE:
269  finalResult.s32 = -finalResult.s32;
270  break;
271  case S64_TYPE:
272  case U64_TYPE:
273  case B64_TYPE:
274  finalResult.s64 = -finalResult.s64;
275  break;
276  case F16_TYPE:
277  finalResult.f16 = -finalResult.f16;
278  break;
279  case F32_TYPE:
280  finalResult.f32 = -finalResult.f32;
281  break;
282  case F64_TYPE:
283  case FF64_TYPE:
284  finalResult.f64 = -finalResult.f64;
285  break;
286  default:
287  assert(0);
288  }
289 
290  }
291 
292  return finalResult;
293 
294 }

296 unsigned get_operand_nbits( const operand_info &op )
297 {
298  if ( op.is_reg() ) {
299  const symbol *sym = op.get_symbol();
300  const type_info *typ = sym->type();
301  type_info_key t = typ->get_key();
302  switch( t.scalar_type() ) {
303  case PRED_TYPE:
304  return 1;
305  case B8_TYPE: case S8_TYPE: case U8_TYPE:
306  return 8;
307  case S16_TYPE: case U16_TYPE: case F16_TYPE: case B16_TYPE:
308  return 16;
309  case S32_TYPE: case U32_TYPE: case F32_TYPE: case B32_TYPE:
310  return 32;
311  case S64_TYPE: case U64_TYPE: case F64_TYPE: case B64_TYPE:
312  return 64;
313  default:
314  printf("ERROR: unknown register type\n");
315  fflush(stdout);
316  abort();
317  }
318  } else {
319  printf("ERROR: Need to implement get_operand_nbits() for currently unsupported operand_info type\n");
320  fflush(stdout);
321  abort();
322  }
323 
324  return 0;
325 }

327 void ptx_thread_info::get_vector_operand_values( const operand_info &op, ptx_reg_t* ptx_regs, unsigned num_elements )
328 {
329  assert( op.is_vector() );
330  assert( num_elements <= 4 ); // max 4 elements in a vector
331 
332  for (int idx = num_elements - 1; idx >= 0; --idx) {
333  const symbol *sym = NULL;
334  sym = op.vec_symbol(idx);
335  if( strcmp(sym->name().c_str(),"_") != 0) {
336  reg_map_t::iterator reg_iter = m_regs.back().find(sym);
337  assert( reg_iter != m_regs.back().end() );
338  ptx_regs[idx] = reg_iter->second;
339  }
340  }
341 }

343 void sign_extend( ptx_reg_t &data, unsigned src_size, const operand_info &dst )
344 {
345  if( !dst.is_reg() )
346  return;
347  unsigned dst_size = get_operand_nbits( dst );
348  if( src_size >= dst_size )
349  return;
350  // src_size < dst_size
351  unsigned long long mask = 1;
352  mask <<= (src_size-1);
353  if( (mask & data.u64) == 0 ) {
354  // no need to sign extend
355  return;
356  }
357  // need to sign extend
358  mask = 1;
359  mask <<= dst_size-src_size;
360  mask -= 1;
361  mask <<= src_size;
362  data.u64 |= mask;
363 }

365 void ptx_thread_info::set_operand_value( const operand_info &dst, const ptx_reg_t &data, unsigned type, ptx_thread_info *thread, const ptx_instruction *pI, int overflow, int carry )
366 {
367  thread->set_operand_value( dst, data, type, thread, pI );
368 
369  if (dst.get_double_operand_type() == -2)
370  {
371  ptx_reg_t predValue;
372 
373  const symbol *sym = dst.vec_symbol(0);
374  predValue.u64 = (m_regs.back()[ sym ].u64) & ~(0x0C);
375  predValue.u64 |= ((overflow & 0x01)<<3);
376  predValue.u64 |= ((carry & 0x01)<<2);
377 
378  set_reg(sym,predValue);
379  }
380  else if (dst.get_double_operand_type() == 0)
381  {
382  //intentionally do nothing
383  }
384  else
385  {
386  printf("Unexpected double destination\n");
387  assert(0);
388  }
389 
390 }

392 void ptx_thread_info::set_operand_value( const operand_info &dst, const ptx_reg_t &data, unsigned type, ptx_thread_info *thread, const ptx_instruction *pI )
393 {
394  ptx_reg_t dstData;
395  memory_space *mem = NULL;
396  size_t size;
397  int t;
398 
399  type_info_key::type_decode(type,size,t);
400 
401  /*complete this section for other cases*/
402  if(dst.get_addr_space() == undefined_space)
403  {
404  ptx_reg_t setValue;
405  setValue.u64 = data.u64;
406 
407  // Double destination in set instruction ($p0|$p1) - second is negation of first
408  if (dst.get_double_operand_type() == -1)
409  {
410  ptx_reg_t setValue2;
411  const symbol *name1 = dst.vec_symbol(0);
412  const symbol *name2 = dst.vec_symbol(1);
413 
414  if ( (type==F16_TYPE)||(type==F32_TYPE)||(type==F64_TYPE)||(type==FF64_TYPE) ) {
415  setValue2.f32 = (setValue.u64==0)?1.0f:0.0f;
416  } else {
417  setValue2.u32 = (setValue.u64==0)?0xFFFFFFFF:0;
418  }
419 
420  set_reg(name1,setValue);
421  set_reg(name2,setValue2);
422  }
423 
424  // Double destination in cvt,shr,mul,etc. instruction ($p0|$r4) - second register operand receives data, first predicate operand
425  // is set as $p0=($r4!=0)
426  // Also for Double destination in set instruction ($p0/$r1)
427  else if ((dst.get_double_operand_type() == -2)||(dst.get_double_operand_type() == -3))
428  {
429  ptx_reg_t predValue;
430  const symbol *predName = dst.vec_symbol(0);
431  const symbol *regName = dst.vec_symbol(1);
432  predValue.u64 = 0;
433 
434  switch ( type ) {
435  case S8_TYPE:
436  if((setValue.s8 & 0x7F) == 0)
437  predValue.u64 |= 1;
438  break;
439  case S16_TYPE:
440  if((setValue.s16 & 0x7FFF) == 0)
441  predValue.u64 |= 1;
442  break;
443  case S32_TYPE:
444  if((setValue.s32 & 0x7FFFFFFF) == 0)
445  predValue.u64 |= 1;
446  break;
447  case S64_TYPE:
448  if((setValue.s64 & 0x7FFFFFFFFFFFFFFF) == 0)
449  predValue.u64 |= 1;
450  break;
451  case U8_TYPE:
452  case B8_TYPE:
453  if(setValue.u8 == 0)
454  predValue.u64 |= 1;
455  break;
456  case U16_TYPE:
457  case B16_TYPE:
458  if(setValue.u16 == 0)
459  predValue.u64 |= 1;
460  break;
461  case U32_TYPE:
462  case B32_TYPE:
463  if(setValue.u32 == 0)
464  predValue.u64 |= 1;
465  break;
466  case U64_TYPE:
467  case B64_TYPE:
468  if(setValue.u64 == 0)
469  predValue.u64 |= 1;
470  break;
471  case F16_TYPE:
472  if(setValue.f16 == 0)
473  predValue.u64 |= 1;
474  break;
475  case F32_TYPE:
476  if(setValue.f32 == 0)
477  predValue.u64 |= 1;
478  break;
479  case F64_TYPE:
480  case FF64_TYPE:
481  if(setValue.f64 == 0)
482  predValue.u64 |= 1;
483  break;
484  default: assert(0); break;
485  }
486 
487 
488  if ( (type==S8_TYPE)||(type==S16_TYPE)||(type==S32_TYPE)||(type==S64_TYPE)||
489  (type==U8_TYPE)||(type==U16_TYPE)||(type==U32_TYPE)||(type==U64_TYPE)||
490  (type==B8_TYPE)||(type==B16_TYPE)||(type==B32_TYPE)||(type==B64_TYPE)) {
491  if((setValue.u32 & (1<<(size-1))) != 0)
492  predValue.u64 |= 1<<1;
493  }
494  if ( type==F32_TYPE ) {
495  if(setValue.f32 < 0)
496  predValue.u64 |= 1<<1;
497  }
498 
499  if(dst.get_operand_lohi() == 1)
500  {
501  setValue.u64 = ((m_regs.back()[ regName ].u64) & (~(0xFFFF))) + (data.u64 & 0xFFFF);
502  }
503  else if(dst.get_operand_lohi() == 2)
504  {
505  setValue.u64 = ((m_regs.back()[ regName ].u64) & (~(0xFFFF0000))) + ((data.u64<<16) & 0xFFFF0000);
506  }
507 
508  set_reg(predName,predValue);
509  set_reg(regName,setValue);
510  }
511  else if (type == BB128_TYPE)
512  {
513  //b128 stuff here.
514  ptx_reg_t setValue2, setValue3, setValue4;
515  setValue.u64 = 0;
516  setValue2.u64 = 0;
517  setValue3.u64 = 0;
518  setValue4.u64 = 0;
519  setValue.u32 = data.u128.lowest;
520  setValue2.u32 = data.u128.low;
521  setValue3.u32 = data.u128.high;
522  setValue4.u32 = data.u128.highest;
523 
524  const symbol *name1, *name2, *name3, *name4 = NULL;
525 
526  name1 = dst.vec_symbol(0);
527  name2 = dst.vec_symbol(1);
528  name3 = dst.vec_symbol(2);
529  name4 = dst.vec_symbol(3);
530 
531  set_reg(name1,setValue);
532  set_reg(name2,setValue2);
533  set_reg(name3,setValue3);
534  set_reg(name4,setValue4);
535  }
536  else if (type == BB64_TYPE || type == FF64_TYPE)
537  {
538  //ptxplus version of storing 64 bit values to registers stores to two adjacent registers
539  ptx_reg_t setValue2;
540  setValue.u32 = 0;
541  setValue2.u32 = 0;
542 
543  setValue.u32 = data.bits.ls;
544  setValue2.u32 = data.bits.ms;
545 
546  const symbol *name1, *name2 = NULL;
547 
548  name1 = dst.vec_symbol(0);
549  name2 = dst.vec_symbol(1);
550 
551  set_reg(name1,setValue);
552  set_reg(name2,setValue2);
553  }
554  else
555  {
556  if(dst.get_operand_lohi() == 1)
557  {
558  setValue.u64 = ((m_regs.back()[ dst.get_symbol() ].u64) & (~(0xFFFF))) + (data.u64 & 0xFFFF);
559  }
560  else if(dst.get_operand_lohi() == 2)
561  {
562  setValue.u64 = ((m_regs.back()[ dst.get_symbol() ].u64) & (~(0xFFFF0000))) + ((data.u64<<16) & 0xFFFF0000);
563  }
564  set_reg(dst.get_symbol(),setValue);
565  }
566  }
567 
568  // global memory - g[4], g[$r0]
569  else if(dst.get_addr_space() == global_space)
570  {
571  dstData = thread->get_operand_value(dst, dst, type, thread, 0);
572  mem = thread->get_global_memory();
573  type_info_key::type_decode(type,size,t);
574 
575  mem->write(dstData.u32,size/8,&data.u128,thread,pI);
576  thread->m_last_effective_address = dstData.u32;
577  thread->m_last_memory_space = global_space;
578  }
579 
580  // shared memory - s[4], s[$r0]
581  else if(dst.get_addr_space() == shared_space)
582  {
583  dstData = thread->get_operand_value(dst, dst, type, thread, 0);
584  mem = thread->m_shared_mem;
585  type_info_key::type_decode(type,size,t);
586 
587  mem->write(dstData.u32,size/8,&data.u128,thread,pI);
588  thread->m_last_effective_address = dstData.u32;
589  thread->m_last_memory_space = shared_space;
590  }
591 
592  // local memory - l0[4], l0[$r0]
593  else if(dst.get_addr_space() == local_space)
594  {
595  dstData = thread->get_operand_value(dst, dst, type, thread, 0);
596  mem = thread->m_local_mem;
597  type_info_key::type_decode(type,size,t);
598 
599  mem->write(dstData.u32,size/8,&data.u128,thread,pI);
600  thread->m_last_effective_address = dstData.u32;
601  thread->m_last_memory_space = local_space;
602  }
603 
604  else
605  {
606  printf("Destination stores to unknown location.");
607  assert(0);
608  }
609 
610 
611 }

636 #define my_abs(a) (((a)<0)?(-a):(a))
637 
638 #define MY_MAX_I(a,b) (a > b) ? a : b
639 #define MY_MAX_F(a,b) isNaN(a) ? b : isNaN(b) ? a : (a > b) ? a : b
640

642 #define MY_MIN_F(a,b) isNaN(a) ? b : isNaN(b) ? a : (a < b) ? a : b
643 
644 #define MY_INC_I(a,b) (a >= b) ? 0 : a+1
645 #define MY_DEC_I(a,b) ((a == 0) || (a > b)) ? b : a-1
646 
647 #define MY_CAS_I(a,b,c) (a == b) ? c : a
648

651 void abs_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
652 {
653  ptx_reg_t a, d;
654  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst();
655  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1();
656 
657  unsigned i_type = pI->get_type();
658  a = thread->get_operand_value(src1, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
659 
660 
661  switch ( i_type ) {
662  case S16_TYPE: d.s16 = my_abs(a.s16); break;
663  case S32_TYPE: d.s32 = my_abs(a.s32); break;
664  case S64_TYPE: d.s64 = my_abs(a.s64); break;
665  case U16_TYPE: d.s16 = my_abs(a.u16); break;
666  case U32_TYPE: d.s32 = my_abs(a.u32); break;
667  case U64_TYPE: d.s64 = my_abs(a.u64); break;
668  case F32_TYPE: d.f32 = my_abs(a.f32); break;
669  case F64_TYPE: case FF64_TYPE: d.f64 = my_abs(a.f64); break;
670  default:
671  printf("Execution error: type mismatch with instruction\n");
672  assert(0);
673  break;
674  }
675 
676  thread->set_operand_value(dst,d, i_type, thread, pI);
677 }

679 void addp_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
680 {
681  //PTXPlus add instruction with carry (carry is kept in a predicate) register
682  ptx_reg_t src1_data, src2_data, src3_data, data;
683  int overflow = 0;
684  int carry = 0;
685 
686  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst(); //get operand info of sources and destination
687  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1(); //use them to determine that they are of type 'register'
688  const operand_info &src2 = pI->src2();
689  const operand_info &src3 = pI->src3();
690 
691  unsigned i_type = pI->get_type();
692  src1_data = thread->get_operand_value(src1, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
693  src2_data = thread->get_operand_value(src2, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
694  src3_data = thread->get_operand_value(src3, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
695 
696  unsigned rounding_mode = pI->rounding_mode();
697  int orig_rm = fegetround();
698  switch ( rounding_mode ) {
699  case RN_OPTION: break;
700  case RZ_OPTION: fesetround( FE_TOWARDZERO ); break;
701  default: assert(0); break;
702  }
703 
704  //performs addition. Sets carry and overflow if needed.
705  //src3_data.pred&0x4 is the carry flag
706  switch ( i_type ) {
707  case S8_TYPE:
708  data.s64 = (src1_data.s64 & 0x0000000FF) + (src2_data.s64 & 0x0000000FF) + (src3_data.pred & 0x4);
709  if(((src1_data.s64 & 0x80)-(src2_data.s64 & 0x80)) == 0) {overflow=((src1_data.s64 & 0x80)-(data.s64 & 0x80))==0?0:1; }
710  carry = (data.u64 & 0x000000100)>>8;
711  break;
712  case S16_TYPE:
713  data.s64 = (src1_data.s64 & 0x00000FFFF) + (src2_data.s64 & 0x00000FFFF) + (src3_data.pred & 0x4);
714  if(((src1_data.s64 & 0x8000)-(src2_data.s64 & 0x8000)) == 0) {overflow=((src1_data.s64 & 0x8000)-(data.s64 & 0x8000))==0?0:1; }
715  carry = (data.u64 & 0x000010000)>>16;
716  break;
717  case S32_TYPE:
718  data.s64 = (src1_data.s64 & 0x0FFFFFFFF) + (src2_data.s64 & 0x0FFFFFFFF) + (src3_data.pred & 0x4);
719  if(((src1_data.s64 & 0x80000000)-(src2_data.s64 & 0x80000000)) == 0) {overflow=((src1_data.s64 & 0x80000000)-(data.s64 & 0x80000000))==0?0:1; }
720  carry = (data.u64 & 0x100000000)>>32;
721  break;
722  case S64_TYPE:
723  data.s64 = src1_data.s64 + src2_data.s64 + (src3_data.pred & 0x4);
724  break;
725  case U8_TYPE:
726  data.u64 = (src1_data.u64 & 0xFF) + (src2_data.u64 & 0xFF) + (src3_data.pred & 0x4);
727  carry = (data.u64 & 0x100)>>8;
728  break;
729  case U16_TYPE:
730  data.u64 = (src1_data.u64 & 0xFFFF) + (src2_data.u64 & 0xFFFF) + (src3_data.pred & 0x4);
731  carry = (data.u64 & 0x10000)>>16;
732  break;
733  case U32_TYPE:
734  data.u64 = (src1_data.u64 & 0xFFFFFFFF) + (src2_data.u64 & 0xFFFFFFFF) + (src3_data.pred & 0x4);
735  carry = (data.u64 & 0x100000000)>>32;
736  break;
737  case U64_TYPE:
738  data.s64 = src1_data.s64 + src2_data.s64 + (src3_data.pred & 0x4);
739  break;
740  case F16_TYPE: assert(0); break;
741  case F32_TYPE: data.f32 = src1_data.f32 + src2_data.f32; break;
742  case F64_TYPE: case FF64_TYPE: data.f64 = src1_data.f64 + src2_data.f64; break;
743  default: assert(0); break;
744  }
745  fesetround( orig_rm );
746 
747  thread->set_operand_value(dst, data, i_type, thread, pI, overflow, carry );
748 }

750 void add_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
751 {
752  ptx_reg_t src1_data, src2_data, data;
753  int overflow = 0;
754  int carry = 0;
755 
756  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst(); //get operand info of sources and destination
757  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1(); //use them to determine that they are of type 'register'

763 
764  unsigned rounding_mode = pI->rounding_mode();

766  switch ( rounding_mode ) {
767  case RN_OPTION: break;

787  carry = (data.u64 & 0x100000000)>>32;

791  break;
792  case U8_TYPE:
793  data.u64 = (src1_data.u64 & 0xFF) + (src2_data.u64 & 0xFF);
794  carry = (data.u64 & 0x100)>>8;
795  break;

802  carry = (data.u64 & 0x100000000)>>32;
803  break;
804  case U64_TYPE:
805  data.u64 = src1_data.u64 + src2_data.u64;
806  break;
807  case F16_TYPE: assert(0); break;
808  case F32_TYPE: data.f32 = src1_data.f32 + src2_data.f32; break;
809  case F64_TYPE: case FF64_TYPE: data.f64 = src1_data.f64 + src2_data.f64; break;
810  default: assert(0); break;
811  }

814  thread->set_operand_value(dst, data, i_type, thread, pI, overflow, carry );

819 void and_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
820 {
821  ptx_reg_t src1_data, src2_data, data;
822 
823  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst();
824  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1();
825  const operand_info &src2 = pI->src2();
826 
827  unsigned i_type = pI->get_type();
828  src1_data = thread->get_operand_value(src1, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
829  src2_data = thread->get_operand_value(src2, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
830 
831 
832  //the way ptxplus handles predicates: 1 = false and 0 = true
833  if(i_type == PRED_TYPE)
834  data.pred = ~(~(src1_data.pred) & ~(src2_data.pred));
835  else
836  data.u64 = src1_data.u64 & src2_data.u64;
837 
838  thread->set_operand_value(dst,data, i_type, thread, pI);

880 void atom_callback( const inst_t* inst, ptx_thread_info* thread)
881 {
882  const ptx_instruction *pI = dynamic_cast<const ptx_instruction*>(inst);
883 
884  // "Decode" the output type
885  unsigned to_type = pI->get_type();
886  size_t size;
887  int t;
888  type_info_key::type_decode(to_type, size, t);
889 
890  // Set up operand variables
891  ptx_reg_t data; // d
892  ptx_reg_t src1_data; // a
893  ptx_reg_t src2_data; // b
894  ptx_reg_t op_result; // temp variable to hold operation result
895 
896  bool data_ready = false;
897 
898  // Get operand info of sources and destination
899  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst(); // d
900  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1(); // a
901  const operand_info &src2 = pI->src2(); // b
902 
903  // Get operand values
904  src1_data = thread->get_operand_value(src1, src1, to_type, thread, 1); // a
905  if (dst.get_symbol()->type()){
906  src2_data = thread->get_operand_value(src2, dst, to_type, thread, 1); // b
907  } else {
908  //This is the case whent he first argument (dest) is '_'
909  src2_data = thread->get_operand_value(src2, src1, to_type, thread, 1); // b
910  }
911 
912  // Check state space
913  addr_t effective_address = src1_data.u64;
914  memory_space_t space = pI->get_space();
915  if (space == undefined_space) {
916  // generic space - determine space via address
917  if( whichspace(effective_address) == global_space ) {
918  effective_address = generic_to_global(effective_address);
919  space = global_space;
920  } else if( whichspace(effective_address) == shared_space ) {
921  unsigned smid = thread->get_hw_sid();
922  effective_address = generic_to_shared(smid,effective_address);
923  space = shared_space;
924  } else {
925  abort();
926  }
927  }
928  assert( space == global_space || space == shared_space );
929 
930  memory_space *mem = NULL;
931  if(space == global_space)
932  mem = thread->get_global_memory();
933  else if(space == shared_space)
934  mem = thread->m_shared_mem;
935  else
936  abort();
937 
938  // Copy value pointed to in operand 'a' into register 'd'
939  // (i.e. copy src1_data to dst)
940  mem->read(effective_address,size/8,&data.s64);
941  if (dst.get_symbol()->type()){
942  thread->set_operand_value(dst, data, to_type, thread, pI); // Write value into register 'd'
943  }
944 
945  // Get the atomic operation to be performed
946  unsigned m_atomic_spec = pI->get_atomic();
947 
948  switch ( m_atomic_spec ) {
949  // AND
950  case ATOMIC_AND:
951  {
952 
953  switch ( to_type ) {
954  case B32_TYPE:
955  case U32_TYPE:
956  op_result.u32 = data.u32 & src2_data.u32;
957  data_ready = true;
958  break;
959  case S32_TYPE:
960  op_result.s32 = data.s32 & src2_data.s32;
961  data_ready = true;
962  break;
963  default:
964  printf("Execution error: type mismatch (%x) with instruction\natom.AND only accepts b32\n", to_type);
965  assert(0);
966  break;
967  }
968 
969  break;
970  }
971  // OR
972  case ATOMIC_OR:
973  {
974 
975  switch ( to_type ) {
976  case B32_TYPE:
977  case U32_TYPE:
978  op_result.u32 = data.u32 | src2_data.u32;
979  data_ready = true;
980  break;
981  case S32_TYPE:
982  op_result.s32 = data.s32 | src2_data.s32;
983  data_ready = true;
984  break;
985  default:
986  printf("Execution error: type mismatch (%x) with instruction\natom.OR only accepts b32\n", to_type);
987  assert(0);
988  break;
989  }
990 
991  break;
992  }
993  // XOR
994  case ATOMIC_XOR:
995  {
996 
997  switch ( to_type ) {
998  case B32_TYPE:
999  case U32_TYPE:
1000  op_result.u32 = data.u32 ^ src2_data.u32;
1001  data_ready = true;
1002  break;
1003  case S32_TYPE:
1004  op_result.s32 = data.s32 ^ src2_data.s32;
1005  data_ready = true;
1006  break;
1007  default:
1008  printf("Execution error: type mismatch (%x) with instruction\natom.XOR only accepts b32\n", to_type);
1009  assert(0);
1010  break;
1011  }
1012 
1013  break;
1014  }
1015  // CAS
1016  case ATOMIC_CAS:
1017  {
1018 
1019  ptx_reg_t src3_data;
1020  const operand_info &src3 = pI->src3();
1021  src3_data = thread->get_operand_value(src3, dst, to_type, thread, 1);
1022 
1023  switch ( to_type ) {
1024  case B32_TYPE:
1025  case U32_TYPE:
1026  op_result.u32 = MY_CAS_I(data.u32, src2_data.u32, src3_data.u32);
1027  data_ready = true;
1028  break;
1029  case B64_TYPE:
1030  case U64_TYPE:
1031  op_result.u64 = MY_CAS_I(data.u64, src2_data.u64, src3_data.u64);
1032  data_ready = true;
1033  break;
1034  case S32_TYPE:
1035  op_result.s32 = MY_CAS_I(data.s32, src2_data.s32, src3_data.s32);
1036  data_ready = true;
1037  break;
1038  default:
1039  printf("Execution error: type mismatch (%x) with instruction\natom.CAS only accepts b32 and b64\n", to_type);
1040  assert(0);
1041  break;
1042  }
1043 
1044  break;
1045  }
1046  // EXCH
1047  case ATOMIC_EXCH:
1048  {
1049  switch ( to_type ) {
1050  case B32_TYPE:
1051  case U32_TYPE:
1052  op_result.u32 = MY_EXCH(data.u32, src2_data.u32);
1053  data_ready = true;
1054  break;
1055  case B64_TYPE:
1056  case U64_TYPE:
1057  op_result.u64 = MY_EXCH(data.u64, src2_data.u64);
1058  data_ready = true;
1059  break;
1060  case S32_TYPE:
1061  op_result.s32 = MY_EXCH(data.s32, src2_data.s32);
1062  data_ready = true;
1063  break;
1064  default:
1065  printf("Execution error: type mismatch (%x) with instruction\natom.EXCH only accepts b32\n", to_type);
1066  assert(0);
1067  break;
1068  }
1069 
1070  break;
1071  }
1072  // ADD
1073  case ATOMIC_ADD:
1074  {
1075 
1076  switch ( to_type ) {
1077  case U32_TYPE:
1078  op_result.u32 = data.u32 + src2_data.u32;
1079  data_ready = true;
1080  break;
1081  case S32_TYPE:
1082  op_result.s32 = data.s32 + src2_data.s32;
1083  data_ready = true;
1084  break;
1085  case U64_TYPE:
1086  op_result.u64 = data.u64 + src2_data.u64;
1087  data_ready = true;
1088  break;
1089  case F32_TYPE:
1090  op_result.f32 = data.f32 + src2_data.f32;
1091  data_ready = true;
1092  break;
1093  default:
1094  printf("Execution error: type mismatch with instruction\natom.ADD only accepts u32, s32, u64, and f32\n");
1095  assert(0);
1096  break;
1097  }
1098 
1099  break;
1100  }
1101  // INC
1102  case ATOMIC_INC:
1103  {
1104  switch ( to_type ) {
1105  case U32_TYPE:
1106  op_result.u32 = MY_INC_I(data.u32, src2_data.u32);
1107  data_ready = true;
1108  break;
1109  default:
1110  printf("Execution error: type mismatch with instruction\natom.INC only accepts u32 and s32\n");
1111  assert(0);
1112  break;
1113  }
1114 
1115  break;
1116  }
1117  // DEC
1118  case ATOMIC_DEC:
1119  {
1120  switch ( to_type ) {
1121  case U32_TYPE:
1122  op_result.u32 = MY_DEC_I(data.u32, src2_data.u32);
1123  data_ready = true;
1124  break;
1125  default:
1126  printf("Execution error: type mismatch with instruction\natom.DEC only accepts u32 and s32\n");
1127  assert(0);
1128  break;
1129  }
1130 
1131  break;
1132  }
1133  // MIN
1134  case ATOMIC_MIN:
1135  {
1136  switch ( to_type ) {
1137  case U32_TYPE:
1138  op_result.u32 = MY_MIN_I(data.u32, src2_data.u32);
1139  data_ready = true;
1140  break;
1141  case S32_TYPE:
1142  op_result.s32 = MY_MIN_I(data.s32, src2_data.s32);
1143  data_ready = true;
1144  break;
1145  default:
1146  printf("Execution error: type mismatch with instruction\natom.MIN only accepts u32 and s32\n");
1147  assert(0);
1148  break;
1149  }
1150 
1151  break;
1152  }
1153  // MAX
1154  case ATOMIC_MAX:
1155  {
1156  switch ( to_type ) {
1157  case U32_TYPE:
1158  op_result.u32 = MY_MAX_I(data.u32, src2_data.u32);
1159  data_ready = true;
1160  break;
1161  case S32_TYPE:
1162  op_result.s32 = MY_MAX_I(data.s32, src2_data.s32);
1163  data_ready = true;
1164  break;
1165  default:
1166  printf("Execution error: type mismatch with instruction\natom.MAX only accepts u32 and s32\n");
1167  assert(0);
1168  break;
1169  }
1170 
1171  break;
1172  }
1173  // DEFAULT
1174  default:
1175  {
1176  assert(0);
1177  break;
1178  }
1179  }
1180 
1181  // Write operation result into memory
1182  // (i.e. copy src1_data to dst)
1183  if ( data_ready ) {
1184  mem->write(effective_address,size/8,&op_result.s64,thread,pI);
1185  } else {
1186  printf("Execution error: data_ready not set\n");
1187  assert(0);
1188  }
1189 }

1191 // atom_impl will now result in a callback being called in mem_ctrl_pop (gpu-sim.c)
1192 void atom_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
1193 {
1194  // SYNTAX
1195  // atom.space.operation.type d, a, b[, c]; (now read in callback)
1196 
1197  // obtain memory space of the operation
1198  memory_space_t space = pI->get_space();
1199 
1200  // get the memory address
1201  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1();
1202  // const operand_info &dst = pI->dst(); // not needed for effective address calculation
1203  unsigned i_type = pI->get_type();
1204  ptx_reg_t src1_data;
1205  src1_data = thread->get_operand_value(src1, src1, i_type, thread, 1);
1206  addr_t effective_address = src1_data.u64;
1207 
1208  addr_t effective_address_final;
1209 
1210  // handle generic memory space by converting it to global
1211  if ( space == undefined_space ) {
1212  if( whichspace(effective_address) == global_space ) {
1213  effective_address_final = generic_to_global(effective_address);
1214  space = global_space;
1215  } else if( whichspace(effective_address) == shared_space ) {
1216  unsigned smid = thread->get_hw_sid();
1217  effective_address_final = generic_to_shared(smid,effective_address);
1218  space = shared_space;
1219  } else {
1220  abort();
1221  }
1222  } else {
1223  assert( space == global_space || space == shared_space );
1224  effective_address_final = effective_address;
1225  }
1226 
1227  // Check state space
1228  assert( space == global_space || space == shared_space );
1229 
1230  thread->m_last_effective_address = effective_address_final;
1231  thread->m_last_memory_space = space;
1232  thread->m_last_dram_callback.function = atom_callback;
1233  thread->m_last_dram_callback.instruction = pI;
1234 }

1236 void bar_impl( const ptx_instruction *pIin, ptx_thread_info *thread )
1237 {
1238  ptx_instruction * pI = const_cast<ptx_instruction *>(pIin);
1239  unsigned bar_op = pI->barrier_op();
1240  unsigned red_op = pI->get_atomic();
1241  unsigned ctaid = thread->get_cta_uid();
1242 
1243  switch(bar_op){
1244  case SYNC_OPTION:
1245  {
1246  if(pI->get_num_operands()>1){
1247  const operand_info &op0 = pI->dst();
1248  const operand_info &op1 = pI->src1();
1249  ptx_reg_t op0_data;
1250  ptx_reg_t op1_data;
1251  op0_data = thread->get_operand_value(op0, op0, U32_TYPE, thread, 1);
1252  op1_data = thread->get_operand_value(op1, op1, U32_TYPE, thread, 1);
1253  pI->set_bar_id(op0_data.u32);
1254  pI->set_bar_count(op1_data.u32);
1255  }else{
1256  const operand_info &op0 = pI->dst();
1257  ptx_reg_t op0_data;
1258  op0_data = thread->get_operand_value(op0, op0, U32_TYPE, thread, 1);
1259  pI->set_bar_id(op0_data.u32);
1260  }
1261  break;
1262  }
1263  case ARRIVE_OPTION:
1264  {
1265  const operand_info &op0 = pI->dst();
1266  const operand_info &op1 = pI->src1();
1267  ptx_reg_t op0_data;
1268  ptx_reg_t op1_data;
1269  op0_data = thread->get_operand_value(op0, op0, U32_TYPE, thread, 1);
1270  op1_data = thread->get_operand_value(op1, op1, U32_TYPE, thread, 1);
1271  pI->set_bar_id(op0_data.u32);
1272  pI->set_bar_count(op1_data.u32);
1273  break;
1274  }
1275  case RED_OPTION:
1276  {
1277  if(pI->get_num_operands()>3){
1278  const operand_info &op1 = pI->src1();
1279  const operand_info &op2 = pI->src2();
1280  const operand_info &op3 = pI->src3();
1281  ptx_reg_t op1_data;
1282  ptx_reg_t op2_data;
1283  ptx_reg_t op3_data;
1284  op1_data = thread->get_operand_value(op1, op1, U32_TYPE, thread, 1);
1285  op2_data = thread->get_operand_value(op2, op2, U32_TYPE, thread, 1);
1286  op3_data = thread->get_operand_value(op3, op3, PRED_TYPE, thread, 1);
1287  op3_data.u32=!(op3_data.pred & 0x0001);
1288  pI->set_bar_id(op1_data.u32);
1289  pI->set_bar_count(op2_data.u32);
1290  switch(red_op){
1291  case ATOMIC_POPC:
1292  thread->popc_reduction(ctaid,op1_data.u32,op3_data.u32);
1293  break;
1294  case ATOMIC_AND:
1295  thread->and_reduction(ctaid,op1_data.u32,op3_data.u32);
1296  break;
1297  case ATOMIC_OR:
1298  thread->or_reduction(ctaid,op1_data.u32,op3_data.u32);
1299  break;
1300  default:
1301  abort();
1302  break;
1303  }
1304  }else{
1305  const operand_info &op1 = pI->src1();
1306  const operand_info &op2 = pI->src2();
1307  ptx_reg_t op1_data;
1308  ptx_reg_t op2_data;
1309  op1_data = thread->get_operand_value(op1, op1, U32_TYPE, thread, 1);
1310  op2_data = thread->get_operand_value(op2, op2, PRED_TYPE, thread, 1);
1311  op2_data.u32=!(op2_data.pred & 0x0001);
1312  pI->set_bar_id(op1_data.u32);
1313  switch(red_op){
1314  case ATOMIC_POPC:
1315  thread->popc_reduction(ctaid,op1_data.u32,op2_data.u32);
1316  break;
1317  case ATOMIC_AND:
1318  thread->and_reduction(ctaid,op1_data.u32,op2_data.u32);
1319  break;
1320  case ATOMIC_OR:
1321  thread->or_reduction(ctaid,op1_data.u32,op2_data.u32);
1322  break;
1323  default:
1324  abort();
1325  break;
1326  }
1327  }
1328  break;
1329  }
1330  default:
1331  abort();
1332  break;
1333  }
1334 
1335  thread->m_last_dram_callback.function = bar_callback;
1336  thread->m_last_dram_callback.instruction = pIin;
1337 }

1380 void call_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
1381 {
1382  static unsigned call_uid_next = 1;
1383 
1384  const operand_info &target = pI->func_addr();
1385  assert( target.is_function_address() );
1386  const symbol *func_addr = target.get_symbol();
1387  const function_info *target_func = func_addr->get_pc();
1388 
1389  // check that number of args and return match function requirements
1390  if( pI->has_return() ^ target_func->has_return() ) {
1391  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: Execution error - mismatch in number of return values between\n"
1392  " call instruction and function declaration\n");
1393  abort();
1394  }
1395  unsigned n_return = target_func->has_return();
1396  unsigned n_args = target_func->num_args();
1397  unsigned n_operands = pI->get_num_operands();
1398 
1399  if( n_operands != (n_return+1+n_args) ) {
1400  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: Execution error - mismatch in number of arguements between\n"
1401  " call instruction and function declaration\n");
1402  abort();
1403  }
1404 
1405  // handle intrinsic functions
1406  std::string fname = target_func->get_name();
1407  if( fname == "vprintf" ) {
1408  gpgpusim_cuda_vprintf(pI, thread, target_func);
1409  return;
1410  }
1411 
1412  // read source arguements into register specified in declaration of function
1413  arg_buffer_list_t arg_values;
1414  copy_args_into_buffer_list(pI, thread, target_func, arg_values);
1415 
1416  // record local for return value (we only support a single return value)
1417  const symbol *return_var_src = NULL;
1418  const symbol *return_var_dst = NULL;
1419  if( target_func->has_return() ) {
1420  return_var_dst = pI->dst().get_symbol();
1421  return_var_src = target_func->get_return_var();
1422  }
1423 
1424  gpgpu_sim *gpu = thread->get_gpu();
1425  unsigned callee_pc=0, callee_rpc=0;
1426  if( gpu->simd_model() == POST_DOMINATOR ) {
1427  thread->get_core()->get_pdom_stack_top_info(thread->get_hw_wid(),&callee_pc,&callee_rpc);
1428  assert( callee_pc == thread->get_pc() );
1429  }
1430 
1431  thread->callstack_push(callee_pc + pI->inst_size(), callee_rpc, return_var_src, return_var_dst, call_uid_next++);
1432 
1433  copy_buffer_list_into_frame(thread, arg_values);
1434 
1435  thread->set_npc(target_func);
1436 }

1461 void clz_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
1462 {

1465  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1();

1492  }

1600 ptx_reg_t f2x( ptx_reg_t x, unsigned from_width, unsigned to_width, int to_sign, int rounding_mode, int saturation_mode )
1601 {
1602  assert( from_width == 32);
1603 
1604  enum cuda_math::cudaRoundMode mode = cuda_math::cudaRoundZero;
1605  switch (rounding_mode) {
1606  case RZI_OPTION: mode = cuda_math::cudaRoundZero; break;
1607  case RNI_OPTION: mode = cuda_math::cudaRoundNearest; break;
1608  case RMI_OPTION: mode = cuda_math::cudaRoundMinInf; break;
1609  case RPI_OPTION: mode = cuda_math::cudaRoundPosInf; break;
1610  default: break;
1611  }
1612 
1613  ptx_reg_t y;
1614  if ( to_sign == 1 ) { // convert to 64-bit number first?
1615  int tmp = cuda_math::float2int(x.f32, mode);
1616  if ((x.u32 & 0x7f800000) == 0)
1617  tmp = 0; // round denorm. FP to 0
1618  if (saturation_mode && to_width < 32) {
1619  tmp = saturatei(tmp, (1<<to_width) - 1, -(1<<to_width));
1620  }
1621  switch ( to_width ) {
1622  case 8: y.s8 = (char)tmp; break;
1623  case 16: y.s16 = (short)tmp; break;
1624  case 32: y.s32 = (int)tmp; break;
1625  case 64: y.s64 = (long long)tmp; break;
1626  default: assert(0); break;
1627  }
1628  } else if ( to_sign == 0 ) {
1629  unsigned int tmp = cuda_math::float2uint(x.f32, mode);
1630  if ((x.u32 & 0x7f800000) == 0)
1631  tmp = 0; // round denorm. FP to 0
1632  if (saturation_mode && to_width < 32) {
1633  tmp = saturatei(tmp, (1<<to_width) - 1);
1634  }
1635  switch ( to_width ) {
1636  case 8: y.u8 = (unsigned char)tmp; break;
1637  case 16: y.u16 = (unsigned short)tmp; break;
1638  case 32: y.u32 = (unsigned int)tmp; break;
1639  case 64: y.u64 = (unsigned long long)tmp; break;
1640  default: assert(0); break;
1641  }
1642  } else {
1643  switch ( to_width ) {
1644  case 16: assert(0); break;
1645  case 32: assert(0); break; // handled by f2f
1646  case 64:
1647  y.f64 = x.f32;
1648  break;
1649  default: assert(0); break;
1650  }
1651  }
1652  return y;
1653 }

1655 double saturated2i (double a, double max, double min) {
1656  if (a > max) a = max;
1657  else if (a < min) a = min;
1658  return a;
1659 }

1661 ptx_reg_t d2x( ptx_reg_t x, unsigned from_width, unsigned to_width, int to_sign, int rounding_mode, int saturation_mode )
1662 {
1663  assert( from_width == 64);
1664 
1665  double tmp;
1666  switch (rounding_mode) {
1667  case RZI_OPTION: tmp = trunc(x.f64); break;
1668  case RNI_OPTION: tmp = nearbyint(x.f64); break;
1669  case RMI_OPTION: tmp = floor(x.f64); break;
1670  case RPI_OPTION: tmp = ceil(x.f64); break;
1671  default: tmp = x.f64; break;
1672  }
1673 
1674  ptx_reg_t y;
1675  if ( to_sign == 1 ) {
1676  tmp = saturated2i(tmp, ((1<<(to_width - 1)) - 1), (1<<(to_width - 1)) );
1677  switch ( to_width ) {
1678  case 8: y.s8 = (char)tmp; break;
1679  case 16: y.s16 = (short)tmp; break;
1680  case 32: y.s32 = (int)tmp; break;
1681  case 64: y.s64 = (long long)tmp; break;
1682  default: assert(0); break;
1683  }
1684  } else if ( to_sign == 0 ) {
1685  tmp = saturated2i(tmp, ((1<<(to_width - 1)) - 1), 0);
1686  switch ( to_width ) {
1687  case 8: y.u8 = (unsigned char)tmp; break;
1688  case 16: y.u16 = (unsigned short)tmp; break;
1689  case 32: y.u32 = (unsigned int)tmp; break;
1690  case 64: y.u64 = (unsigned long long)tmp; break;
1691  default: assert(0); break;
1692  }
1693  } else {
1694  switch ( to_width ) {
1695  case 16: assert(0); break;
1696  case 32:
1697  y.f32 = x.f64;
1698  break;
1699  case 64:
1700  y.f64 = x.f64; // should be handled by d2d
1701  break;
1702  default: assert(0); break;
1703  }
1704  }
1705  return y;
1706 }

1739  }
1740  break;

1792 ptx_reg_t f2f( ptx_reg_t x, unsigned from_width, unsigned to_width, int to_sign, int rounding_mode, int saturation_mode )
1793 {
1794  ptx_reg_t y;
1795  switch ( rounding_mode ) {
1796  case RZI_OPTION:
1797  y.f32 = truncf(x.f32);
1798  break;
1799  case RNI_OPTION:
1800 #if CUDART_VERSION >= 3000
1801  y.f32 = nearbyintf(x.f32);
1802 #else
1803  y.f32 = cuda_math::__internal_nearbyintf(x.f32);
1804 #endif
1805  break;
1806  case RMI_OPTION:
1807  if ((x.u32 & 0x7f800000) == 0) {
1808  y.u32 = x.u32 & 0x80000000; // round denorm. FP to 0, keeping sign
1809  } else {
1810  y.f32 = floorf(x.f32);
1811  }
1812  break;
1813  case RPI_OPTION:
1814  if ((x.u32 & 0x7f800000) == 0) {
1815  y.u32 = x.u32 & 0x80000000; // round denorm. FP to 0, keeping sign
1816  } else {
1817  y.f32 = ceilf(x.f32);
1818  }
1819  break;
1820  default:
1821  if ((x.u32 & 0x7f800000) == 0) {
1822  y.u32 = x.u32 & 0x80000000; // round denorm. FP to 0, keeping sign
1823  } else {
1824  y.f32 = x.f32;
1825  }
1826  break;
1827  }
1828 #if CUDART_VERSION >= 3000
1829  if (isnanf(y.f32))
1830 #else
1831  if (cuda_math::__cuda___isnanf(y.f32))
1832 #endif
1833  {
1834  y.u32 = 0x7fffffff;
1835  } else if (saturation_mode) {
1836  y.f32 = cuda_math::__saturatef(y.f32);
1837  }
1838 
1839  return y;
1840 }

1889 void ptx_round(ptx_reg_t& data, int rounding_mode, int type)
1890 {
1891  if (rounding_mode == RN_OPTION) {
1892  return;
1893  }
1894  switch ( rounding_mode ) {
1895  case RZI_OPTION:
1896  switch ( type ) {
1897  case S8_TYPE:
1898  case S16_TYPE:
1899  case S32_TYPE:
1900  case S64_TYPE:
1901  case U8_TYPE:
1902  case U16_TYPE:
1903  case U32_TYPE:
1904  case U64_TYPE:
1905  printf("Trying to round an integer??\n"); assert(0); break;
1906  case F16_TYPE: assert(0); break;
1907  case F32_TYPE:
1908  data.f32 = truncf(data.f32);
1909  break;
1910  case F64_TYPE:
1911  case FF64_TYPE:
1912  if (data.f64 < 0) data.f64 = ceil(data.f64); //negative
1913  else data.f64 = floor(data.f64); //positive
1914  break;
1915  default: assert(0); break;
1916  }
1917  break;
1918  case RNI_OPTION:
1919  switch ( type ) {
1920  case S8_TYPE:
1921  case S16_TYPE:
1922  case S32_TYPE:
1923  case S64_TYPE:
1924  case U8_TYPE:
1925  case U16_TYPE:
1926  case U32_TYPE:
1927  case U64_TYPE:
1928  printf("Trying to round an integer??\n"); assert(0); break;
1929  case F16_TYPE: assert(0); break;
1930  case F32_TYPE:
1931 #if CUDART_VERSION >= 3000
1932  data.f32 = nearbyintf(data.f32);
1933 #else
1934  data.f32 = cuda_math::__cuda_nearbyintf(data.f32);
1935 #endif
1936  break;
1937  case F64_TYPE: case FF64_TYPE: data.f64 = round(data.f64); break;
1938  default: assert(0); break;
1939  }
1940  break;
1941  case RMI_OPTION:
1942  switch ( type ) {
1943  case S8_TYPE:
1944  case S16_TYPE:
1945  case S32_TYPE:
1946  case S64_TYPE:
1947  case U8_TYPE:
1948  case U16_TYPE:
1949  case U32_TYPE:
1950  case U64_TYPE:
1951  printf("Trying to round an integer??\n"); assert(0); break;
1952  case F16_TYPE: assert(0); break;
1953  case F32_TYPE:
1954  data.f32 = floorf(data.f32);
1955  break;
1956  case F64_TYPE: case FF64_TYPE: data.f64 = floor(data.f64); break;
1957  default: assert(0); break;
1958  }
1959  break;
1960  case RPI_OPTION:
1961  switch ( type ) {
1962  case S8_TYPE:
1963  case S16_TYPE:
1964  case S32_TYPE:
1965  case S64_TYPE:
1966  case U8_TYPE:
1967  case U16_TYPE:
1968  case U32_TYPE:
1969  case U64_TYPE:
1970  printf("Trying to round an integer??\n"); assert(0); break;
1971  case F16_TYPE: assert(0); break;
1972  case F32_TYPE: data.f32 = ceilf(data.f32); break;
1973  case F64_TYPE: case FF64_TYPE: data.f64 = ceil(data.f64); break;
1974  default: assert(0); break;
1975  }
1976  break;
1977  default: break;
1978  }
1979 
1980  if (type == F32_TYPE) {
1981 #if CUDART_VERSION >= 3000
1982  if (isnanf(data.f32))
1983 #else
1984  if (cuda_math::__cuda___isnanf(data.f32))
1985 #endif
1986  {
1987  data.u32 = 0x7fffffff;
1988  }
1989  }
1990  if ((type == F64_TYPE)||(type == FF64_TYPE)) {
1991  if (isnan(data.f64)) {
1992  data.u64 = 0xfff8000000000000ull;
1993  }
1994  }
1995 }

1997 void ptx_saturate(ptx_reg_t& data, int saturation_mode, int type)
1998 {
1999  if (!saturation_mode) {
2000  return;
2001  }
2002  switch ( type ) {
2003  case S8_TYPE:
2004  case S16_TYPE:
2005  case S32_TYPE:
2006  case S64_TYPE:
2007  case U8_TYPE:
2008  case U16_TYPE:
2009  case U32_TYPE:
2010  case U64_TYPE:
2011  printf("Trying to clamp an integer to 1??\n"); assert(0); break;
2012  case F16_TYPE: assert(0); break;
2013  case F32_TYPE:
2014  if (data.f32 > 1.0f) data.f32 = 1.0f; //negative
2015  if (data.f32 < 0.0f) data.f32 = 0.0f; //positive
2016  break;
2017  case F64_TYPE:
2018  case FF64_TYPE:
2019  if (data.f64 > 1.0f) data.f64 = 1.0f; //negative
2020  if (data.f64 < 0.0f) data.f64 = 0.0f; //positive
2021  break;
2022  default: assert(0); break;
2023  }

2245 void decode_space( memory_space_t &space, ptx_thread_info *thread, const operand_info &op, memory_space *&mem, addr_t &addr)
2246 {
2247  unsigned smid = thread->get_hw_sid();
2248  unsigned hwtid = thread->get_hw_tid();
2249 
2250  if( space == param_space_unclassified ) {
2251  // need to op to determine whether it refers to a kernel param or local param
2252  const symbol *s = op.get_symbol();
2253  const type_info *t = s->type();
2254  type_info_key ti = t->get_key();
2255  if( ti.is_param_kernel() )
2256  space = param_space_kernel;
2257  else if( ti.is_param_local() ) {
2258  space = param_space_local;
2259  } else {
2260  printf("GPGPU-Sim PTX: ERROR ** cannot resolve .param space for '%s'\n", s->name().c_str() );
2261  abort();
2262  }
2263  }
2264  switch ( space.get_type() ) {
2265  case global_space: mem = thread->get_global_memory(); break;
2266  case param_space_local:
2267  case local_space:
2268  mem = thread->m_local_mem;
2269  addr += thread->get_local_mem_stack_pointer();
2270  break;
2271  case tex_space: mem = thread->get_tex_memory(); break;
2272  case surf_space: mem = thread->get_surf_memory(); break;
2273  case param_space_kernel: mem = thread->get_param_memory(); break;
2274  case shared_space: mem = thread->m_shared_mem; break;
2275  case const_space: mem = thread->get_global_memory(); break;
2276  case generic_space:
2277  if( thread->get_ptx_version().ver() >= 2.0 ) {
2278  // convert generic address to memory space address
2279  space = whichspace(addr);
2280  switch ( space.get_type() ) {
2281  case global_space: mem = thread->get_global_memory(); addr = generic_to_global(addr); break;
2282  case local_space: mem = thread->m_local_mem; addr = generic_to_local(smid,hwtid,addr); break;
2283  case shared_space: mem = thread->m_shared_mem; addr = generic_to_shared(smid,addr); break;
2284  default: abort();
2285  }
2286  } else {
2287  abort();
2288  }
2289  break;
2290  case param_space_unclassified:
2291  case undefined_space:
2292  default:
2293  abort();
2294  }
2295 }

2429 void mad_def( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread, bool use_carry )
2430 {
2431  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst();
2432  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1();
2433  const operand_info &src2 = pI->src2();
2434  const operand_info &src3 = pI->src3();
2435  ptx_reg_t d, t;
2436 
2437  int carry=0;
2438  int overflow=0;
2439 
2440  unsigned i_type = pI->get_type();
2441  ptx_reg_t a = thread->get_operand_value(src1, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
2442  ptx_reg_t b = thread->get_operand_value(src2, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
2443  ptx_reg_t c = thread->get_operand_value(src3, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
2444 
2445  // take the carry bit, it should be the 4th operand
2446  ptx_reg_t carry_bit;
2447  carry_bit.u64 = 0;
2448  if (use_carry) {
2449  const operand_info &carry = pI->operand_lookup(4);
2450  carry_bit = thread->get_operand_value(carry, dst, PRED_TYPE, thread, 0);
2451  carry_bit.pred &= 0x4;
2452  carry_bit.pred >>=2;
2453  }
2454 
2455  unsigned rounding_mode = pI->rounding_mode();
2456 
2457  switch ( i_type ) {
2458  case S16_TYPE:
2459  t.s32 = a.s16 * b.s16;
2460  if ( pI->is_wide() ) d.s32 = t.s32 + c.s32 + carry_bit.pred;
2461  else if ( pI->is_hi() ) d.s16 = (t.s32>>16) + c.s16 + carry_bit.pred;
2462  else if ( pI->is_lo() ) d.s16 = t.s16 + c.s16 + carry_bit.pred;
2463  else assert(0);
2464  carry = ((long long int)(t.s32 + c.s32 + carry_bit.pred)&0x100000000)>>32;
2465  break;
2466  case S32_TYPE:
2467  t.s64 = a.s32 * b.s32;
2468  if ( pI->is_wide() ) d.s64 = t.s64 + c.s64 + carry_bit.pred;
2469  else if ( pI->is_hi() ) d.s32 = (t.s64>>32) + c.s32 + carry_bit.pred;
2470  else if ( pI->is_lo() ) d.s32 = t.s32 + c.s32 + carry_bit.pred;
2471  else assert(0);
2472  break;
2473  case S64_TYPE:
2474  t.s64 = a.s64 * b.s64;
2475  assert( !pI->is_wide() );
2476  assert( !pI->is_hi() );
2477  assert( use_carry == false);
2478  if ( pI->is_lo() ) d.s64 = t.s64 + c.s64 + carry_bit.pred;
2479  else assert(0);
2480  break;
2481  case U16_TYPE:
2482  t.u32 = a.u16 * b.u16;
2483  if ( pI->is_wide() ) d.u32 = t.u32 + c.u32 + carry_bit.pred;
2484  else if ( pI->is_hi() ) d.u16 = (t.u32 + c.u16 + carry_bit.pred)>>16;
2485  else if ( pI->is_lo() ) d.u16 = t.u16 + c.u16 + carry_bit.pred;
2486  else assert(0);
2487  carry = ((long long int)((long long int)t.u32 + c.u32 + carry_bit.pred)&0x100000000)>>32;
2488  break;
2489  case U32_TYPE:
2490  t.u64 = a.u32 * b.u32;
2491  if ( pI->is_wide() ) d.u64 = t.u64 + c.u64 + carry_bit.pred;
2492  else if ( pI->is_hi() ) d.u32 = (t.u64 + c.u32 + carry_bit.pred)>>32;
2493  else if ( pI->is_lo() ) d.u32 = t.u32 + c.u32 + carry_bit.pred;
2494  else assert(0);
2495  break;
2496  case U64_TYPE:
2497  t.u64 = a.u64 * b.u64;
2498  assert( !pI->is_wide() );
2499  assert( !pI->is_hi() );
2500  assert( use_carry == false);
2501  if ( pI->is_lo() ) d.u64 = t.u64 + c.u64 + carry_bit.pred;
2502  else assert(0);
2503  break;
2504  case F16_TYPE:
2505  assert(0);
2506  break;
2507  case F32_TYPE: {
2508  assert( use_carry == false);
2509  int orig_rm = fegetround();
2510  switch ( rounding_mode ) {
2511  case RN_OPTION: break;
2512  case RZ_OPTION: fesetround( FE_TOWARDZERO ); break;
2513  default: assert(0); break;
2514  }
2515  d.f32 = a.f32 * b.f32 + c.f32;
2516  if ( pI->saturation_mode() ) {
2517  if ( d.f32 < 0 ) d.f32 = 0;
2518  else if ( d.f32 > 1.0f ) d.f32 = 1.0f;
2519  }
2520  fesetround( orig_rm );
2521  break;
2522  }
2523  case F64_TYPE: case FF64_TYPE: {
2524  assert( use_carry == false);
2525  int orig_rm = fegetround();
2526  switch ( rounding_mode ) {
2527  case RN_OPTION: break;
2528  case RZ_OPTION: fesetround( FE_TOWARDZERO ); break;
2529  default: assert(0); break;
2530  }
2531  d.f64 = a.f64 * b.f64 + c.f64;
2532  if ( pI->saturation_mode() ) {
2533  if ( d.f64 < 0 ) d.f64 = 0;
2534  else if ( d.f64 > 1.0f ) d.f64 = 1.0;
2535  }
2536  fesetround( orig_rm );
2537  break;
2538  }
2539  default:
2540  assert(0);
2541  break;
2542  }
2543  thread->set_operand_value(dst, d, i_type, thread, pI, overflow, carry);
2544 }

2621 void mov_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
2622 {
2623  ptx_reg_t data;
2624 
2625  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst();
2626  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1();
2627  unsigned i_type = pI->get_type();
2628 
2629  if( (src1.is_vector() || dst.is_vector()) && (i_type != BB64_TYPE) && (i_type != BB128_TYPE) && (i_type != FF64_TYPE) ) {
2630  // pack or unpack operation
2631  unsigned nbits_to_move;
2632  ptx_reg_t tmp_bits;
2633 
2634  switch( pI->get_type() ) {
2635  case B16_TYPE: nbits_to_move = 16; break;
2636  case B32_TYPE: nbits_to_move = 32; break;
2637  case B64_TYPE: nbits_to_move = 64; break;
2638  default: printf("Execution error: mov pack/unpack with unsupported type qualifier\n"); assert(0); break;
2639  }
2640 
2641  if( src1.is_vector() ) {
2642  unsigned nelem = src1.get_vect_nelem();
2643  ptx_reg_t v[4];
2644  thread->get_vector_operand_values(src1, v, nelem );
2645 
2646  unsigned bits_per_src_elem = nbits_to_move / nelem;
2647  for( unsigned i=0; i < nelem; i++ ) {
2648  switch(bits_per_src_elem) {
2649  case 8: tmp_bits.u64 |= ((unsigned long long)(v[i].u8) << (8*i)); break;
2650  case 16: tmp_bits.u64 |= ((unsigned long long)(v[i].u16) << (16*i)); break;
2651  case 32: tmp_bits.u64 |= ((unsigned long long)(v[i].u32) << (32*i)); break;
2652  default: printf("Execution error: mov pack/unpack with unsupported source/dst size ratio (src)\n"); assert(0); break;
2653  }
2654  }
2655  } else {
2656  data = thread->get_operand_value(src1, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
2657 
2658  switch( pI->get_type() ) {
2659  case B16_TYPE: tmp_bits.u16 = data.u16; break;
2660  case B32_TYPE: tmp_bits.u32 = data.u32; break;
2661  case B64_TYPE: tmp_bits.u64 = data.u64; break;
2662  default: assert(0); break;
2663  }
2664  }
2665 
2666  if( dst.is_vector() ) {
2667  unsigned nelem = dst.get_vect_nelem();
2668  ptx_reg_t v[4];
2669  unsigned bits_per_dst_elem = nbits_to_move / nelem;
2670  for( unsigned i=0; i < nelem; i++ ) {
2671  switch(bits_per_dst_elem) {
2672  case 8: v[i].u8 = (tmp_bits.u64 >> (8*i)) & ((unsigned long long) 0xFF); break;
2673  case 16: v[i].u16 = (tmp_bits.u64 >> (16*i)) & ((unsigned long long) 0xFFFF); break;
2674  case 32: v[i].u32 = (tmp_bits.u64 >> (32*i)) & ((unsigned long long) 0xFFFFFFFF); break;
2675  default:
2676  printf("Execution error: mov pack/unpack with unsupported source/dst size ratio (dst)\n");
2677  assert(0);
2678  break;
2679  }
2680  }
2681  thread->set_vector_operand_values(dst,v[0],v[1],v[2],v[3]);
2682  } else {
2683  thread->set_operand_value(dst,tmp_bits, i_type, thread, pI);
2684  }
2685  } else if (i_type == PRED_TYPE and src1.is_literal() == true) {
2686  // in ptx, literal input translate to predicate as 0 = false and 1 = true
2687  // we have adopted the opposite to simplify implementation of zero flags in ptxplus
2688  data = thread->get_operand_value(src1, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
2689 
2690  ptx_reg_t finaldata;
2691  finaldata.pred = (data.u32 == 0)? 1 : 0; // setting zero-flag in predicate
2692  thread->set_operand_value(dst, finaldata, i_type, thread, pI);
2693  } else {
2694 
2695  data = thread->get_operand_value(src1, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
2696 
2697  thread->set_operand_value(dst, data, i_type, thread, pI);
2698 
2699  }
2700 }

2702 void mul24_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
2703 {
2704  ptx_reg_t src1_data, src2_data, data;

2706  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst();

2748 void mul_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
2749 {
2750  ptx_reg_t data;
2751 
2752  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst();
2753  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1();
2754  const operand_info &src2 = pI->src2();

2756

2758  ptx_reg_t a = thread->get_operand_value(src1, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
2759  ptx_reg_t b = thread->get_operand_value(src2, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
2760 
2761  unsigned rounding_mode = pI->rounding_mode();
2762 
2763  switch ( i_type ) {
2764  case S16_TYPE:
2765  t.s32 = ((int)a.s16) * ((int)b.s16);
2766  if ( pI->is_wide() ) d.s32 = t.s32;
2767  else if ( pI->is_hi() ) d.s16 = (t.s32>>16);
2768  else if ( pI->is_lo() ) d.s16 = t.s16;
2769  else assert(0);
2770  break;
2771  case S32_TYPE:
2772  t.s64 = ((long long)a.s32) * ((long long)b.s32);
2773  if ( pI->is_wide() ) d.s64 = t.s64;
2774  else if ( pI->is_hi() ) d.s32 = (t.s64>>32);
2775  else if ( pI->is_lo() ) d.s32 = t.s32;
2776  else assert(0);
2777  break;
2778  case S64_TYPE:
2779  t.s64 = a.s64 * b.s64;
2780  assert( !pI->is_wide() );
2781  assert( !pI->is_hi() );

2783  else assert(0);
2784  break;

2788  else if ( pI->is_lo() ) d.u16 = t.u16;
2789  else if ( pI->is_hi() ) d.u16 = (t.u32>>16);
2790  else assert(0);
2791  break;
2792  case U32_TYPE:
2793  t.u64 = ((unsigned long long)a.u32) * ((unsigned long long)b.u32);
2794  if ( pI->is_wide() ) d.u64 = t.u64;
2795  else if ( pI->is_lo() ) d.u32 = t.u32;
2796  else if ( pI->is_hi() ) d.u32 = (t.u64>>32);
2797  else assert(0);
2798  break;
2799  case U64_TYPE:
2800  t.u64 = a.u64 * b.u64;
2801  assert( !pI->is_wide() );
2802  assert( !pI->is_hi() );
2803  if ( pI->is_lo() ) d.u64 = t.u64;
2804  else assert(0);
2805  break;
2806  case F16_TYPE:
2807  assert(0);
2808  break;
2809  case F32_TYPE: {
2810  int orig_rm = fegetround();
2811  switch ( rounding_mode ) {
2812  case RN_OPTION: break;
2813  case RZ_OPTION: fesetround( FE_TOWARDZERO ); break;
2814  default: assert(0); break;
2815  }
2816 
2817  d.f32 = a.f32 * b.f32;
2818 
2819  if ( pI->saturation_mode() ) {
2820  if ( d.f32 < 0 ) d.f32 = 0;
2821  else if ( d.f32 > 1.0f ) d.f32 = 1.0f;
2822  }
2823  fesetround( orig_rm );
2824  break;
2825  }
2826  case F64_TYPE: case FF64_TYPE:{
2827  int orig_rm = fegetround();
2828  switch ( rounding_mode ) {
2829  case RN_OPTION: break;
2830  case RZ_OPTION: fesetround( FE_TOWARDZERO ); break;
2831  default: assert(0); break;
2832  }
2833  d.f64 = a.f64 * b.f64;
2834  if ( pI->saturation_mode() ) {
2835  if ( d.f64 < 0 ) d.f64 = 0;
2836  else if ( d.f64 > 1.0f ) d.f64 = 1.0;
2837  }
2838  fesetround( orig_rm );
2839  break;
2840  }
2841  default:
2842  assert(0);
2843  break;
2844  }

3203 bool CmpOp( int type, ptx_reg_t a, ptx_reg_t b, unsigned cmpop )
3204 {
3205  bool t = false;
3206 
3207  switch ( type ) {
3208  case B16_TYPE:
3209  switch (cmpop) {
3210  case EQ_OPTION: t = (a.u16 == b.u16); break;
3211  case NE_OPTION: t = (a.u16 != b.u16); break;
3212  default:
3213  assert(0);
3214  }
3215 
3216  case B32_TYPE:
3217  switch (cmpop) {
3218  case EQ_OPTION: t = (a.u32 == b.u32); break;
3219  case NE_OPTION: t = (a.u32 != b.u32); break;
3220  default:
3221  assert(0);
3222  }
3223  case B64_TYPE:
3224  switch (cmpop) {
3225  case EQ_OPTION: t = (a.u64 == b.u64); break;
3226  case NE_OPTION: t = (a.u64 != b.u64); break;
3227  default:
3228  assert(0);
3229  }
3230  break;
3231  case S8_TYPE:
3232  case S16_TYPE:
3233  switch (cmpop) {
3234  case EQ_OPTION: t = (a.s16 == b.s16); break;
3235  case NE_OPTION: t = (a.s16 != b.s16); break;
3236  case LT_OPTION: t = (a.s16 < b.s16); break;
3237  case LE_OPTION: t = (a.s16 <= b.s16); break;
3238  case GT_OPTION: t = (a.s16 > b.s16); break;
3239  case GE_OPTION: t = (a.s16 >= b.s16); break;
3240  default:
3241  assert(0);
3242  }
3243  break;
3244  case S32_TYPE:
3245  switch (cmpop) {
3246  case EQ_OPTION: t = (a.s32 == b.s32); break;
3247  case NE_OPTION: t = (a.s32 != b.s32); break;

3715 void sub_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
3716 {
3717  ptx_reg_t data;
3718  int overflow = 0;
3719  int carry = 0;
3720 
3721  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst();
3722  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1();
3723  const operand_info &src2 = pI->src2();
3724 
3725  unsigned i_type = pI->get_type();
3726  ptx_reg_t src1_data = thread->get_operand_value(src1, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
3727  ptx_reg_t src2_data = thread->get_operand_value(src2, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
3728 
3729  //performs addition. Sets carry and overflow if needed.
3730  //the constant is added in during subtraction so the carry bit is set properly.
3731  switch ( i_type ) {
3732  case S8_TYPE:
3733  data.s64 = (src1_data.s64 & 0xFF) - (src2_data.s64 & 0xFF) + 0x100;
3734  if(((src1_data.s64 & 0x80)-(src2_data.s64 & 0x80)) != 0) {overflow=((src1_data.s64 & 0x80)-(data.s64 & 0x80))==0?0:1; }
3735  carry = (data.s32 & 0x100)>>8;
3736  break;
3737  case S16_TYPE:
3738  data.s64 = (src1_data.s64 & 0xFFFF) - (src2_data.s64 & 0xFFFF) + 0x10000;
3739  if(((src1_data.s64 & 0x8000)-(src2_data.s64 & 0x8000)) != 0) {overflow=((src1_data.s64 & 0x8000)-(data.s64 & 0x8000))==0?0:1; }
3740  carry = (data.s32 & 0x10000)>>16;
3741  break;
3742  case S32_TYPE:
3743  data.s64 = (src1_data.s64 & 0xFFFFFFFF) - (src2_data.s64 & 0xFFFFFFFF) + 0x100000000;
3744  if(((src1_data.s64 & 0x80000000)-(src2_data.s64 & 0x80000000)) != 0) {overflow=((src1_data.s64 & 0x80000000)-(data.s64 & 0x80000000))==0?0:1; }
3745  carry = ((data.u64)>>32) & 0x0001;
3746  break;
3747  case S64_TYPE:
3748  data.s64 = src1_data.s64 - src2_data.s64; break;
3749  case B8_TYPE:
3750  case U8_TYPE:
3751  data.u64 = (src1_data.u64 & 0xFF) - (src2_data.u64 & 0xFF) + 0x100;
3752  carry = (data.u64 & 0x100)>>8;
3753  break;
3754  case B16_TYPE:
3755  case U16_TYPE:
3756  data.u64 = (src1_data.u64 & 0xFFFF) - (src2_data.u64 & 0xFFFF) + 0x10000;
3757  carry = (data.u64 & 0x10000)>>16;
3758  break;
3759  case B32_TYPE:
3760  case U32_TYPE:
3761  data.u64 = (src1_data.u64 & 0xFFFFFFFF) - (src2_data.u64 & 0xFFFFFFFF) + 0x100000000;
3762  carry = (data.u64 & 0x100000000)>>32;
3763  break;
3764  case B64_TYPE:
3765  case U64_TYPE:
3766  data.u64 = src1_data.u64 - src2_data.u64; break;
3767  case F16_TYPE: assert(0); break;
3768  case F32_TYPE: data.f32 = src1_data.f32 - src2_data.f32; break;
3769  case F64_TYPE: case FF64_TYPE: data.f64 = src1_data.f64 - src2_data.f64; break;
3770  default: assert(0); break;
3771  }
3772 
3773  thread->set_operand_value(dst,data, i_type, thread, pI, overflow, carry);
3774 }

3790  int a;
3791  float b;

3794 float reduce_precision( float x, unsigned bits )
3795 {
3796  intfloat tmp;
3797  tmp.b = x;
3798  int v = tmp.a;
3799  int man = v & ((1<<23)-1);
3800  int mask = ((1<<bits)-1) << (23-bits);
3801  int nv = (v & ((-1)-((1<<23)-1))) | (mask&man);
3802  tmp.a = nv;
3803  float result = tmp.b;
3804  return result;
3805 }

3810  unsigned ny = (my+y)%my;

3815 {
3816  unsigned nx = x;
3817  while (nx >= mx) nx -= elem_size;
3818  unsigned ny = (y >= my)? my - 1 : y;

3822 typedef unsigned (*texAddr_t) (unsigned x, unsigned y, unsigned mx, unsigned my, size_t elem_size);
3823 float tex_linf_sampling(memory_space* mem, unsigned tex_array_base,
3824  int x, int y, unsigned int width, unsigned int height, size_t elem_size,
3825  float alpha, float beta, texAddr_t b_lim)
3826 {
3827  float Tij;
3828  float Ti1j;
3829  float Tij1;
3830  float Ti1j1;
3831 
3832  mem->read(tex_array_base + b_lim(x,y,width,height,elem_size), 4, &Tij);
3833  mem->read(tex_array_base + b_lim(x+elem_size,y,width,height,elem_size), 4, &Ti1j);
3834  mem->read(tex_array_base + b_lim(x,y+1,width,height,elem_size), 4, &Tij1);
3835  mem->read(tex_array_base + b_lim(x+elem_size,y+1,width,height,elem_size), 4, &Ti1j1);
3836 
3837  float sample = (1-alpha)*(1-beta)*Tij +
3838  alpha*(1-beta)*Ti1j +
3839  (1-alpha)*beta*Tij1 +
3840  alpha*beta*Ti1j1;
3841 
3842  return sample;
3843 }

3845 float textureNormalizeElementSigned(int element, int bits)
3846 {
3847  if (bits) {
3848  int maxN = (1 << bits) - 1;
3849  // removing upper bits
3850  element &= maxN;
3851  // normalizing the number to [-1.0,1.0]
3852  maxN >>= 1;
3853  float output = (float) element / maxN;
3854  if (output < -1.0f) output = -1.0f;
3855  return output;
3856  } else {
3857  return 0.0f;
3858  }
3859 }
3860 
3861 float textureNormalizeElementUnsigned(unsigned int element, int bits)
3862 {
3863  if (bits) {
3864  unsigned int maxN = (1 << bits) - 1;
3865  // removing upper bits and normalizing the number to [0.0,1.0]
3866  return (float)(element & maxN) / maxN;
3867  } else {
3868  return 0.0f;
3869  }
3870 }

3878  dataw.f32 = textureNormalizeElementSigned( dataw.s32, desc.w );

3881  datay.f32 = textureNormalizeElementUnsigned( datay.u32, desc.y );
3882  dataz.f32 = textureNormalizeElementUnsigned( dataz.u32, desc.z );
3883  dataw.f32 = textureNormalizeElementUnsigned( dataw.u32, desc.w );
3884  } else {
3885  assert(0 && "Undefined texture read mode: cudaReadModeNormalizedFloat expect integer elements");
3886  }
3887 }

3961  alpha = x_f32 - floor(x_f32); // offset into subtexel (for linear sampling)
3962  x = (int) x_f32;

3966  // handle texture fetch that exceeded boundaries
3967  if (texref->addressMode[0] == cudaAddressModeClamp) {

3969  x = (x < 0)? 0 : x;

3971  x = x % width;
3972  }

3977

3981  height = cuArray->height;

3990  x_f32 = x_f32 - floor(x_f32);
3991  }
3992  if (texref->addressMode[1]) {//clamp

4000  float xb = x_f32 * width - 0.5;
4001  float yb = y_f32 * height - 0.5;

4174 void vote_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
4175 {
4176  static bool first_in_warp = true;
4177  static bool and_all;
4178  static bool or_all;
4179  static unsigned int ballot_result;
4180  static std::list<ptx_thread_info*> threads_in_warp;
4181  static unsigned last_tid;
4182 
4183  if( first_in_warp ) {
4184  first_in_warp = false;
4185  threads_in_warp.clear();
4186  and_all = true;
4187  or_all = false;
4188  ballot_result = 0;
4189  int offset=31;
4190  while( (offset>=0) && !pI->active(offset) )
4191  offset--;
4192  assert( offset >= 0 );
4193  last_tid = (thread->get_hw_tid() - (thread->get_hw_tid()%pI->warp_size())) + offset;
4194  }
4195 
4196  ptx_reg_t src1_data;
4197  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1();
4198  src1_data = thread->get_operand_value(src1, pI->dst(), PRED_TYPE, thread, 1);
4199 
4200  //predicate value was changed so the lowest bit being set means the zero flag is set.
4201  //As a result, the value of src1_data.pred must be inverted to get proper behavior
4202  bool pred_value = !(src1_data.pred & 0x0001);
4203  bool invert = src1.is_neg_pred();
4204 
4205  threads_in_warp.push_back(thread);
4206  and_all &= (invert ^ pred_value);
4207  or_all |= (invert ^ pred_value);
4208 
4209  // vote.ballot
4210  if (invert ^ pred_value) {
4211  int lane_id = thread->get_hw_tid() % pI->warp_size();
4212  ballot_result |= (1 << lane_id);
4213  }
4214 
4215  if( thread->get_hw_tid() == last_tid ) {
4216  if (pI->vote_mode() == ptx_instruction::vote_ballot) {
4217  ptx_reg_t data = ballot_result;
4218  for( std::list<ptx_thread_info*>::iterator t=threads_in_warp.begin(); t!=threads_in_warp.end(); ++t ) {
4219  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst();
4220  (*t)->set_operand_value(dst,data, pI->get_type(), (*t), pI);
4221  }
4222  } else {
4223  bool pred_value = false;
4224 
4225  switch( pI->vote_mode() ) {
4226  case ptx_instruction::vote_any: pred_value = or_all; break;
4227  case ptx_instruction::vote_all: pred_value = and_all; break;
4228  case ptx_instruction::vote_uni: pred_value = (or_all ^ and_all); break;
4229  default:
4230  abort();
4231  }
4232  ptx_reg_t data;
4233  data.pred = pred_value?0:1; //the way ptxplus handles the zero flag, 1 = false and 0 = true
4234 
4235  for( std::list<ptx_thread_info*>::iterator t=threads_in_warp.begin(); t!=threads_in_warp.end(); ++t ) {
4236  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst();
4237  (*t)->set_operand_value(dst,data, PRED_TYPE, (*t), pI);
4238  }
4239  }
4240  first_in_warp = true;
4241  }
4242 }
4243 
4244 void xor_impl( const ptx_instruction *pI, ptx_thread_info *thread )
4245 {
4246  ptx_reg_t src1_data, src2_data, data;
4247 
4248  const operand_info &dst = pI->dst();
4249  const operand_info &src1 = pI->src1();
4250  const operand_info &src2 = pI->src2();
4251 
4252  unsigned i_type = pI->get_type();
4253  src1_data = thread->get_operand_value(src1, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
4254  src2_data = thread->get_operand_value(src2, dst, i_type, thread, 1);
4255 
4256  //the way ptxplus handles predicates: 1 = false and 0 = true
4257  if(i_type == PRED_TYPE)
4258  data.pred = ~(~(src1_data.pred) ^ ~(src2_data.pred));
4259  else
4260  data.u64 = src1_data.u64 ^ src2_data.u64;
4261 
4262  thread->set_operand_value(dst,data, i_type, thread, pI);
4263 }

4274 ptx_reg_t srcOperandModifiers(ptx_reg_t opData, operand_info opInfo, operand_info dstInfo, unsigned type, ptx_thread_info *thread)
4275 {
4276  ptx_reg_t result;
4277  memory_space *mem = NULL;
4278  size_t size;
4279  int t;
4280  result.u64=0;
4281 
4282  //complete other cases for reading from memory, such as reading from other const memory
4283  if(opInfo.get_addr_space() == global_space)
4284  {
4285  mem = thread->get_global_memory();
4286  type_info_key::type_decode(type,size,t);
4287  mem->read(opData.u32,size/8,&result.u64);
4288  if( type == S16_TYPE || type == S32_TYPE )
4289  sign_extend(result,size,dstInfo);
4290  }
4291  else if(opInfo.get_addr_space() == shared_space)
4292  {
4293  mem = thread->m_shared_mem;
4294  type_info_key::type_decode(type,size,t);
4295  mem->read(opData.u32,size/8,&result.u64);
4296 
4297  if( type == S16_TYPE || type == S32_TYPE )
4298  sign_extend(result,size,dstInfo);
4299 
4300  }
4301  else if(opInfo.get_addr_space() == const_space)
4302  {
4303  mem = thread->get_global_memory();
4304  type_info_key::type_decode(type,size,t);
4305 
4306  mem->read((opData.u32 + opInfo.get_const_mem_offset()),size/8,&result.u64);
4307 
4308  if( type == S16_TYPE || type == S32_TYPE )
4309  sign_extend(result,size,dstInfo);
4310  }
4311  else
4312  {
4313  result = opData;
4314  }
4315 
4316  if(opInfo.get_operand_lohi() == 1)
4317  {
4318  result.u64 = result.u64 & 0xFFFF;
4319  }
4320  else if(opInfo.get_operand_lohi() == 2)
4321  {
4322  result.u64 = (result.u64>>16) & 0xFFFF;
4323  }
4324 
4325  if(opInfo.get_operand_neg() == true) {
4326  result.f32 = -result.f32;
4327  }
4328 
4329  return result;
4330 }
